text: were this marketed for a different segment, directed with skill and integrity, and acted better... it would still rather suck because it's so predictable.   there are just too many LOL moments of character and plot stupidity to take this thing seriously. that's a shame, too, because the political and power-grab subplots might have been interesting were they not so obvious and handled in a ham-fisted manner.  do i want my two bucks back from red box? no, but only because i found entertainment value in mocking it. to be fair, though, the whole premise of this story from the start is utterly ridiculous and is only moreso as it's progressed.  why are these movies so bad? i think it's to appeal to the demographic they're aimed for, a demographic who would be turned off were these movies not interchangeable in almost every fashion as opposed to being artfully done requiring experience and maturity to appreciate finer details of cinema. in other words, this tripe appeals to those too young to know the difference between good and bad storytelling, character development and overall movie-making.
